data.name: RevisionTag
desc: represents the information that describes a revision of something.

items.name: Author
lines: contains an identifier for the author that created the revision( can be empty )

items.name: Comment
lines: contains a comment that the author has left for this revision ( can be empty )

items.name: Identifier
lines: contains a unique identifier for the revision and must not be empty
This identifier can have any form. It can be something like "1.2.3" or "Version 1" etc. It depends on the revision control system how it names the revisions.

items.name: TimeStamp
lines: contains the time when the revision was created ( can be invalid )
